The authors conclude that ‘this retroperception effect demonstrates that postcued attention can retrospectively trigger the conscious perception of a stimulus that would otherwise have escaped consciousness’. 
33. van Gaal S, Scholte HS, Lamme VA, Fahrenfort JJ, Ridderinkhof KR: Pre-SMA graymatter density predicts individual differences in action selection in the face of conscious and unconscious response conflict. 
