This important event-related potential study extends an earlier study by Del Cul et al. (2007, Ref. 
[60]). 
It replicates the finding that conscious visual perception of brief unexpected stimuli is associated primarily with a late P300 potential, but also shows that the neural correlates of conscious perception shift to an earlier time period (the P2) when the identity of the stimulus is fully expected. 
